<item>
            <title>[FLINK-11253] Incorrect way to stop yarn session described in yarn_setup document</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-11253</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are two ways to stop yarn session described in yarn_setup document:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Stop the YARN session by stopping the unix process (using CTRL+C) or by entering &#8216;stop&#8217; into the client.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But in fact, yarn session application still can run after stopping the unix process (using CTRL+C).&lt;br/&gt;
We can either update the yarn_setup document to remove this incorrect way or add ShutdownHook to stop yarn session in FlinkYarnSessionCli to make it correct.&lt;br/&gt;
Looking forward to the feedbacks and would like to work on this ticket. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
